              >
            </div>
            <div class="integrations-tabs-content w-tab-content">
              <div data-w-tab="Description" class="integration-tab w-tab-pane w--tab-active">
                <div class="rich-text w-richtext">
                  <p>
                    Badges.ninja is a complete digital badge platform for organizations that need verifiable,
                    portable credentials. It combines a visual designer, a REST API, and optional on-chain anchoring
                    to produce credentials that recipients can share anywhere — and anyone can verify in seconds.
                  </p>
                  <h3><strong>Features</strong></h3>
                  <ul role="list">
                    <li>
                      <strong>Visual Badge Designer</strong><br />A canvas editor with 80+ starter templates
                      (8 shapes &times; 8 palettes), filter chips, custom text, fonts, icons, and image uploads.
                      Build branded badges without leaving the dashboard.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Open Badge v2.0 Compliant</strong><br />Every credential follows the Open Badges
                      standard — portable across LinkedIn, learning platforms, and any verifier that understands
                      OBv2.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Bulk Awarding</strong><br />Issue thousands of awards at once by uploading a CSV.
                      The issuance pipeline supports pause, resume, and retry so large cohorts land cleanly.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Blockchain Verification</strong><br />Optional on-chain anchoring on Matchain
                      (available on paid plans). Every anchored award carries a tamper-proof hash verifiable by
                      anyone.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>REST API with X-Api-Key</strong><br />A clean REST API available on every plan, keyed
                      per account (<em>bws_&hellip;</em> format). Automate issuer setup, badge creation, awards,
                      and revocation from your stack. Public verification endpoints require no auth at all.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>IPFS Image Storage</strong><br />Badge images are pinned to IPFS for permanent,
                      decentralized storage — so a credential's visual never disappears behind a dead link.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>LinkedIn Add-to-Profile</strong><br />One-click &ldquo;Add to LinkedIn&rdquo; button
                      on every public award page, optimized for recipient sharing.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Recipient Portal</strong><br />Passwordless sign-in at <em>badges.ninja/me</em>, with
                      optional public profiles at <em>badges.ninja/u/&lt;handle&gt;</em> where recipients collect
                      everything they've earned.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>PDF Certificates &amp; QR Verification</strong><br />Every award includes a
                      downloadable A4 PDF certificate and a scannable QR code on the public page for offline
                      verification.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Free Tier</strong><br />100 awards per month included at signup — no credit card
                      required. Scale to unlimited awards on Starter and Pro plans when you need more.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                  <h3><strong>How It Works</strong></h3>
                  <ul role="list">
                    <li>
                      <strong>1. Create an Issuer</strong><br />Set up your organization profile (name, website,
                      contact email, logo). Issuers matching your account email auto-verify.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>2. Design a Badge</strong><br />Draft a credential template — title, description,
                      earning criteria, and image — in the visual designer. The image is pinned to IPFS on save.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>3. Award It</strong><br />Issue to individual recipients or upload a CSV for bulk.
                      Each award gets a unique verification URL, a PDF certificate, a QR code, and — optionally —
                      an on-chain anchor.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>4. Share &amp; Verify</strong><br />Recipients share via email, social media, or a
                      single click to LinkedIn. Anyone can verify the credential through the public URL or by
                      scanning the QR code.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                  <h3><strong>Use Cases</strong></h3>
                  <ul role="list">
                    <li>
                      <strong>Learning &amp; Certification</strong><br />Courses, bootcamps, and training programs
                      issuing verifiable completion credentials at scale.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Professional Associations</strong><br />Membership and accreditation badges with
                      blockchain-backed tamper-proof records.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Events &amp; Conferences</strong><br />Attendance, speaker, and sponsorship badges
                      issued in bulk and shareable straight to LinkedIn.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Enterprise Recognition</strong><br />Internal skills credentials, compliance
                      certifications, and employee achievements with durable verification.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                  <p>
                    Badges.ninja removes the friction of building a credentialing stack: visual design, standards
                    compliance, blockchain verification, and a recipient experience polished enough to share on
                    LinkedIn in one click.
                  </p>
                </div>
